name: TheAtlantic
text: “Pandemic school is clearly not working well, especially for younger children,” @ErikaChristakis writes. But parents are coming to understand that school was not always working so great before COVID-19 either. https://t.co/4NXzwicpAi

name: TheAtlantic
text: Coronavirus hospitalizations hit a record high in the United States today, making it clear that the country has entered the worst moment in the pandemic since the spring, @alexismadrigal and @kissane write: https://t.co/tuXwmoJois

name: TheAtlantic
text: "There will be a path to ending the pandemic, but it will be fraught." A COVID-19 vaccine finally looks likely, but can a Biden administration convince Americans to take it? @sarahzhang reports: https://t.co/FffhDmfb52

name: TheAtlantic
text: Republican women in America’s suburbs helped make Joe Biden president, @elainejgodfrey reports. So ... are they Democrats now? https://t.co/dt8QG0UsnX

name: TheAtlantic
text: Democrats set aside their differences to elect Joe Biden. Now that he's won, that detente is over, @elainejgodfrey reports. https://t.co/MACe7VvRI6

name: TheAtlantic
text: When the exhaustion clears, some liberals will miss Trump, argues @helenlewis. Or rather, they will miss the moral clarity that opposing him brought. When you’re used to fighting enemies, how do you go back to having mere opponents? https://t.co/LpV57Oqu4J

name: TheAtlantic
text: "If the Court invalidates the law, the result will be extremely grim: Without the federal funding that supports the law’s coverage expansions, millions of Americans will quickly lose their health insurance," @nicholas_bagley writes: https://t.co/aMdFLpCXWX

name: TheAtlantic
text: If the pandemic didn't persuade everyone to support science in the election, can anything? @jameshamblin writes: https://t.co/8fLbwn3nay

name: TheAtlantic
text: When radiation from Jupiter meets the icy surface of one of the most fascinating moons in the solar system, it could create an unusual light, @marinakoren writes. https://t.co/xV2dMJtM13

name: TheAtlantic
text: Alex Trebek made a mundane game magnificent, and the people who played it stars. As the host of “Jeopardy,” he pulled off a tricky feat: He made trivia nerds look cool, argues @mansee_writes. "Simply by hosting a quiz show, Trebek changed lives." https://t.co/5rBbKE1S9L

name: TheAtlantic
text: RT @prashantrao: "With Joe Biden soon to take over the White House, Europe has lost its unifying bogeyman. The question for the Continent’s leaders now is whether they can agree on what they are collectively for, not just what they are against." Always read @TomMcTague https://t.co/oN5aFl6c4v

name: TheAtlantic
text: "Even though the election results do not appear to be in doubt, what Trump and his team are doing now is corrosive to democracy," @rickhasen writes: https://t.co/oSKHOwioKV

name: TheAtlantic
text: Black voters saved Biden's campaign, and then helped him win the general election. Now they'll push him to make good on his promises, @AdamHSays writes: https://t.co/FSEbYMbRXP
